This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.2.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/HACKING for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.2.1:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r14885
    Python bindings, fix for functions returning MD5 digests.
    Justification:
      Small change, potentially useful, 1.3 is quite some way off.
    Votes:
      +1: maxb, dlr
      
  * r15088
    Make lock/unlock over ra_dav able to cache authentication data.
    Justfication: Users of locking over http:// will get very annoyed.
    Votes:
      +1: kfogel, sussman

  * r15119
    Fix an off-by-one error in svn_repos_get_logs3.
    Justification: API correctness
    Votes:
      +1: clkao (non-binding), kfogel

  * r15082
    Perl bindings, svn_lock_t related accessors.
    Justifcation: Bindings completeness
    Votes:
      +1: clkao

  * r15080, r15081, r15117
    Perl bindings, call utf_initialize, adjust global pool usage
    Justification: Performance issue for binding users in non-utf8 locale
    Votes:
      +1: clkao

  * r15157
    Fix Issue #2343: svn_io_copy_dir_recursively is broken
    Justifcation: Prevents a rather simple operation from completing if the
    source path contains the same name as the destination.
    Votes:
      +1: jszakmeister

Approved changes (further review is welcome, but not required):
